{
  "texts": [
    "Overall, combining VR with generative AI would help in enabling realistic simulations for practice, improving task speed, accuracy, and trainee satisfaction, ultimately improving surgical planning and setting new standards for surgical training [112].In addition to VR, augmented reality (AR) holds significant potential to improve surgical training within orthopedics.",
    "Unlike traditional virtual reality (VR) simulators, which create entirely virtual environments, AR enhances the real world by superimposing computer-generated information onto actual objects [115,116], allowing surgeons to maintain spatial awareness while interacting with real tools and anatomy [117].",
    "This feature significantly benefits surgical training, offering an immersive experience that combines real-world tactility with enriched, interactive visual guidance [117].",
    "For instance, AR-based simulators allow the use of actual surgical instruments, improving skill acquisition in areas such as hand-eye coordination, accuracy, and bimanual dexterity [118,119].",
    "Innocente et al."
  ]
}